comments: During the screen, Paul (PHX) and Fournier (ORL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
Paul (PHX) makes contact with Fournier's (ORL) arm at the end of his drive and the contact affects his ability to cleanly gather the ball.
During the inbound, Carter-Williams (ORL) disengages with Paul (PHX) and establishes himself in Ayton's (PHX) path to absorb the contact on the screen.

Vucevic (ORL) establishes himself in post position and has his arm extended out for the entry pass when marginal contact occurs to Bridges' (PHX) head.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Crowder (PHX) legally contests Gordon's (ORL) jump shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) establishes himself in a screening position in Carter-Williams' (ORL) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.

During the rebound, Ayton (PHX) has his arms resting on Carter-Williams' (PHX) back and marginal contact occurs as Ayton releases back towards the ball.  The reaction from Carter-Williams is not consistent with the amount of contact.
During the screen, Ayton (PHX) and Vucevic (ORL) engage and disengage and the contact is marginal.
At the end of the drive, Fournier (ORL) stops his forward momentum by planting his left foot and releasing from the contact with Crowder (PHX), prior to the step back jump shot attempt.
Fournier (ORL) applies a forearm to Booker's (PHX) side and delivers contact, prior to the start of his upward shooting motion.
During the screen, Ayton (PHX) delivers contact to Vucevic's (ORL) back that dislodges him from his legally obtained position.
Carter-Williams (ORL) turns into and makes contact with Booker's (PHX) body that affects his driving shot attempt.
Ayton (PHX) has a resting hand to Fournier's (ORL) side and the contact is marginal during Fournier's driving shot attempt.
Booker (PHX) has his arms extended out and collapses them in as he absorbs the contact from Fournier (ORL) on his driving shot attempt.
After the inbound, Fournier (ORL) and Booker (PHX) engage and disengage and marginal contact occurs prior to Fournier cleanly deflecting the ball out of bounds.
During the inbound, Fournier (ORL) and Booker (PHX) engage and disengage and the marginal contact does not affect Booker's ability to get to the pass.
Vucevic (ORL) maintains a legal guarding position during the driving shot attempt by Booker (PHX).
The game clock expires prior to Booker (PHX) making any contact with Vucevic (ORL) on his attempted take foul.
